{\par \b Syntax:}\par WAIT(n)\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Halts program execution for the specified number of seconds.\par If n is omitted or 0, halts execution until the user presses a key and returns the keycode (or -1 after 1 minute).\par \par If n is -1, halts executions until the user presses a key or there is a mouse event.\par If a key is pressed, the keycode is returned.\par After a 1 minute timeout, returns -1\par \par If a mouse event happends, a list of the form \{ type, [x, y], [dx, dy] \} is returned. Normally x/y is the event position unless otherwise indicated.\par Type can be:\par 0: Mouse Down\par 1: Mouse Move\par 2: Mouse Up (x/y is not provided)\par 3: Mouse Click (note, if a click is detected, there is no MouseUp)\par 5: Mouse Stretch. x/y is the delta since the last event. dx/dy is the delta since the ORIGINAL mouse down...\par 6: Mouse Rotate, x is original angle, y is new angle in 32nd of a circle.\par 7: Mouse Long Click, This means that the mouse stayed down for 1 second...\par
{\par \b Example:}\par WAIT(5) halts program execution for 5 seconds.\par }